=== Trace of a square matrix ===
The trace formula_23 of a square matrix formula_24 is the sum of all elements on its main diagonal. Matrices can be multiplied by scalars and two matrices of the same dimension can be added together; these operations make a vector space from the set of all formula_25 matrices. The trace is a linear functional on this space because formula_26 and formula_27 for all scalars formula_28 and all formula_25 matrices formula_30

=== (Definite) Integration ===
Linear functionals first appeared in functional analysis, the study of vector spaces of functions. A typical example of a linear functional is integration: the linear transformation defined by the Riemann integral
formula_31
is a linear functional from the vector space formula_32 of continuous functions on the interval formula_33 to the real numbers. The linearity of formula_34 follows from the standard facts about the integral:
formula_35

=== Evaluation ===
Let formula_36 denote the vector space of real-valued polynomial functions of degree formula_37 defined on an interval formula_38 If formula_39 then let formula_40 be the evaluation functional
