If formula_44 are formula_45 distinct points in formula_46 then the evaluation functionals formula_47 formula_48 form a basis of the dual space of formula_36 ( proves this last fact using Lagrange interpolation).

=== Non-example ===
A function formula_50 having the equation of a line formula_51 with formula_52 (for example, formula_53) is a linear functional on formula_54, since it is not linear. It is, however, affine-linear.

== Visualization ==
In finite dimensions, a linear functional can be visualized in terms of its level sets, the sets of vectors which map to a given value. In three dimensions, the level sets of a linear functional are a family of mutually parallel planes; in higher dimensions, they are parallel hyperplanes. This method of visualizing linear functionals is sometimes introduced in general relativity texts, such as &quot;Gravitation&quot; by .

== Applications ==

=== Application to quadrature ===
If formula_44 are formula_45 distinct points in , then the linear functionals formula_57 defined above form a basis of the dual space of , the space of polynomials of degree formula_58 The integration functional is also a linear functional on , and so can be expressed as a linear combination of these basis elements. In symbols, there are coefficients formula_59 for which
formula_60
for all formula_61 This forms the foundation of the theory of numerical quadrature.

=== In quantum mechanics ===
Linear functionals are particularly important in quantum mechanics. Quantum mechanical systems are represented by Hilbert spaces, which are anti–isomorphic to their own dual spaces. A state of a quantum mechanical system can be identified with a linear functional. For more information see bra–ket notation.

=== Distributions ===
In the theory of generalized functions, certain kinds of generalized functions called distributions can be realized as linear functionals on spaces of test functions.

==Dual vectors and bilinear forms==
