Every linear functional on formula_87 is complex-valued while every linear functional on formula_90 is real-valued. If formula_100 then a linear functional on either one of formula_87 or formula_90 is non-trivial (meaning not identically formula_103) if and only if it is surjective (because if formula_104 then for any scalar formula_105 formula_106), where the image of a linear functional on formula_87 is formula_108 while the image of a linear functional on formula_90 is formula_110 
