For any subset of formula_257 the following are equivalent: 
# is equicontinuous;
# is contained in the polar of some neighborhood of formula_103 in ;
# the (pre)polar of is a neighborhood of formula_103 in ;

If is an equicontinuous subset of formula_260 then the following sets are also equicontinuous: 
the weak-* closure, the balanced hull, the convex hull, and the convex balanced hull. 
Moreover, Alaoglu&#x27;s theorem implies that the weak-* closure of an equicontinuous subset of formula_260 is weak-* compact (and thus that every equicontinuous subset weak-* relatively compact).

